get a little bit more information on that, but essentially yes we did, because that's

1523
00:56:23,402 --> 00:56:24,543
the only way you're going to be able to do this.

1524
00:56:24,583 --> 00:56:28,206
Like if you have enemies all swarming you and no way to control it, it just is unplayable,

1525
00:56:28,226 --> 00:56:29,066
so we've always had that.

1526
00:56:32,574 --> 00:56:36,057
Hi, thank you for your talk. My question is about Atreus.

1527
00:56:36,117 --> 00:56:41,142
So how did you balance him to not take away intentionality from the player?

1528
00:56:41,282 --> 00:56:44,424
Say, for example, I'm waiting for an enemy to attack me and I really want to parry him.

1529
00:56:45,946 --> 00:56:48,928
But then before that happens, Atreus stuns him.

1530
00:56:49,494 --> 00:56:50,195
Oh, right, yeah, yeah.

1531
00:56:50,495 --> 00:56:57,339
So the question is, how do we prevent Atreus from just screwing you over half the time?

1532
00:56:57,379 --> 00:57:00,701
So this was actually a big part of Atreus' design in a lot of the iteration, because

1533
00:57:00,761 --> 00:57:05,504
a lot of the things that Atreus does is designed to not take him away from your position.

1534
00:57:05,844 --> 00:57:08,166
So a good example is when he comes up and he grabs a guy.

1535
00:57:08,426 --> 00:57:11,688
When he does that, all he's doing is making it easier to hit the guy that's already right

1536
00:57:11,708 --> 00:57:12,148
in front of me.

1537
00:57:12,168 --> 00:57:14,750
He's not pushing him aside or doing anything that's going to stop my view.

1538
00:57:15,230 --> 00:57:18,272
Similarly, if I'm pointing my reticle at an enemy, that would be the worst time for Kratos

1539
00:57:18,292 --> 00:57:18,492
to do that.

1540
00:57:18,953 --> 00:57:20,434
sorry, Atreus to knock him out the way.

1541
00:57:20,834 --> 00:57:22,335
So we have a lot of checks to make sure

1542
00:57:22,355 --> 00:57:24,757
that what Atreus does actually only enhances

1543
00:57:24,998 --> 00:57:26,219
what I'm probably already doing.

1544
00:57:26,579 --> 00:57:28,440
So another good example is if I knock the guy away

1545
00:57:28,500 --> 00:57:30,662
and he lands over here, it's fine for Atreus

1546
00:57:30,682 --> 00:57:32,223
to come here and just kind of beat him down.

1547
00:57:32,664 --> 00:57:34,686
But if he moves him, then that's gonna probably

1548
00:57:34,726 --> 00:57:36,387
screw me up if I was gonna evade and follow him.

1549
00:57:36,887 --> 00:57:39,189
So we try to make sure that everything Atreus does

1550
00:57:39,269 --> 00:57:40,730
is just an enhancement on what I'm doing

1551
00:57:40,771 --> 00:57:41,671
so he never gets in the way.

1552
00:57:42,472 --> 00:57:42,692
Thanks.

1553
00:57:44,503 --> 00:57:46,665
Hi, you mentioned at a certain point,

1554
00:57:46,685 --> 00:57:49,908
switching to multiple different resources in combat.

1555
00:57:50,589 --> 00:57:53,452
And I'm wondering if you ever got to a place

1556
00:57:53,512 --> 00:57:55,413
where you were worried that you had too many

1557
00:57:55,554 --> 00:57:58,036
or where players would be confused

1558
00:57:58,116 --> 00:58:00,038
by all the different element options.

1559
00:58:00,238 --> 00:58:01,740
And if not, how did you avoid that?

1560
00:58:02,163 --> 00:58:06,785
Yeah, yeah. So the question was, once we started adding all the damage types and various things

1561
00:58:06,825 --> 00:58:11,987
in the game, what happens, when did it become too complicated or were we afraid of that?

1562
00:58:12,427 --> 00:58:16,549
And the answer to that, I think, is the entire studio is constantly afraid of that, especially

1563
00:58:16,569 --> 00:58:20,850
if you're not a combat designer. Everybody else is just always scared about everything

1564
00:58:20,870 --> 00:58:23,271
you're going to add, especially if they're playing the game themselves and they're not

1565
00:58:23,311 --> 00:58:23,912
doing those things.

1566
00:58:24,352 --> 00:58:29,054
So that's where playtests help a lot, because we had about 20 people each time coming in

1567
00:58:29,194 --> 00:58:33,016
playing the game, and then you would hopefully see within those 20 people a variety of things

1568
00:58:33,036 --> 00:58:37,199
that they're doing, because again, you don't expect just in one play session for everybody

1569
00:58:37,239 --> 00:58:41,241
to gravitate towards everything, but everybody has their own play styles, and you try to

1570
00:58:41,281 --> 00:58:43,362
put things in the game that contribute to that play style.

1571
00:58:43,862 --> 00:58:48,626
So, we would look at that and try to see if players would start to gravitate towards it.

1572
00:58:49,107 --> 00:58:52,850
And if we started to see things to be a bit too complicated, meaning that we'd ask them

1573
00:58:52,890 --> 00:58:56,453
and see if they understand this and they already have no idea, we either try to simplify it

1574
00:58:56,493 --> 00:58:57,954
or make it so they can understand.

1575
00:58:58,534 --> 00:59:02,377
But so much of my answer to the other question is like, we were okay if you didn't know some

1576
00:59:02,397 --> 00:59:02,637
things.

1577
00:59:04,279 --> 00:59:04,499
Thank you.

1578
00:59:05,544 --> 00:59:06,766
Hey Jason, thanks so much for your talk.

1579
00:59:06,826 --> 00:59:08,367
It's good to see some of the magic behind the scenes.

1580
00:59:09,068 --> 00:59:12,973
My question is regarding how this combat system interfaced with bosses.

1581
00:59:13,253 --> 00:59:15,936
Were there any special considerations or adaptations you had to make?

1582
00:59:16,336 --> 00:59:19,300
Yes, absolutely. I mean the bosses, especially the big bosses like the dragon,

1583
00:59:19,520 --> 00:59:22,503
they always have their own kind of system in terms of how they're going to attack you

1584
00:59:22,523 --> 00:59:24,165
because they're kind of outside the combat system.

1585
00:59:25,085 --> 00:59:31,627
Thankfully, other characters like the Stranger, no spoilers, but the Stranger, he was an enemy

1586
00:59:31,647 --> 00:59:35,908
that was in our combat system, so we always have special considerations for any special

1587
00:59:36,368 --> 00:59:39,949
case things that need to happen, but generally characters like that operate within the combat

1588
00:59:39,989 --> 00:59:40,189
system.

1589
00:59:44,420 --> 00:59:50,042
Great talk, thank you very much. I've been playing God of War since God of War 1 back in, I don't know, when I was young I guess.

1590
00:59:50,563 --> 00:59:57,206
