1591
00:59:58,206 --> 01:00:02,908
Jumping into this game, obviously from the get-go you can't play the game on the hardest difficulty because it's like, you're clearly not ready!

1592
01:00:03,228 --> 01:00:08,491
But like, I jumped into the difficulty above normal, and it demolished me.

1593
01:00:09,559 --> 01:00:12,500
So I don't know if I'm just like Kratos, really old and angry,

1594
01:00:12,740 --> 01:00:14,801
or if it's something that, a big thing I noticed

1595
01:00:14,841 --> 01:00:16,722
about the difficulty was that it sort of just extended

1596
01:00:16,762 --> 01:00:19,163
enemy life bars to make them take a lot more hits

1597
01:00:19,223 --> 01:00:20,584
as opposed to other games that have just made it

1598
01:00:20,624 --> 01:00:22,305
to where the time to kill is the same,

1599
01:00:22,325 --> 01:00:23,425
but the damage outputs are higher,

1600
01:00:23,445 --> 01:00:24,706
so there's a lot more risk and reward.

1601
01:00:24,866 --> 01:00:26,506
Was there a lot of talk in the studio

1602
01:00:26,546 --> 01:00:27,907
of doing that deliberately for the purpose

1603
01:00:27,927 --> 01:00:29,988
of a lot of the juggling mechanics you were talking about?

1604
01:00:30,279 --> 01:00:31,900
Oh yeah, I mean there's a lot of gameplay tuning.

1605
01:00:31,940 --> 01:00:36,524
I mean I can say that we didn't really extend a character's life bars just to make more

1606
01:00:36,624 --> 01:00:37,305
juggling happen.

1607
01:00:37,785 --> 01:00:41,028
But usually what we're trying to do is we're trying to emphasize some of the more deliberate

1608
01:00:41,068 --> 01:00:41,669
decision making.

1609
01:00:41,849 --> 01:00:45,492
So ideas like, oh I can launch a guy and throw the axe at him into a wall for an instant

1610
01:00:45,512 --> 01:00:45,692
kill.

1611
01:00:45,712 --> 01:00:46,873
It doesn't matter how much health they have.

1612
01:00:47,394 --> 01:00:49,235
Things like that were things that we were trying to promote

1613
01:00:49,335 --> 01:00:50,356
on some of the harder difficulties.

1614
01:00:50,376 --> 01:00:52,037
So we would tune their health up slightly,

1615
01:00:52,458 --> 01:00:53,478
but hopefully not too slightly

1616
01:00:53,518 --> 01:00:54,519
that it felt like you couldn't win,

1617
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:57,241
but more so that we wanted you to kind of take part

1618
01:00:57,301 --> 01:00:58,422
in some of those deliberate decisions

1619
01:00:58,462 --> 01:00:59,363
that I was talking about.

1620
01:00:59,663 --> 01:01:01,925
So like in that example where you could freeze a guy

1621
01:01:01,945 --> 01:01:03,586
and kick an enemy into multiple guys,

1622
01:01:03,927 --> 01:01:05,908
that gives you a lot of time to kind of make these decisions

1623
01:01:05,948 --> 01:01:06,909
but if you don't do that,

1624
01:01:07,249 --> 01:01:08,690
it probably will be a rough experience.

1625
01:01:11,733 --> 01:01:13,454
Oh, I think we're out of time.

1626
01:01:13,694 --> 01:01:14,215
So thank you.

